title: Get help with your online Home Office application

heading_context: Get help with your online Home Office application
What type of help you can get
chunks.html_content:
If you’re in the UK, you can get help filling in your online Home Office application if you:

  • do not feel confident using a computer or mobile device
  • do not have internet access
  • do not have access to a device like a laptop or smart phone

This is known as ‘Assisted Digital’ support and can be used for help with any Home Office application, for example:

  • the EU Settlement Scheme
  • British citizenship
  • a Student visa - if your sponsor cannot help
  • a Skilled Worker visa - if your sponsor cannot help

You can get:

  • phone support from an advisor
  • face to face support in person

‘We Are Group’ will assess your eligibility and provide support.

heading_context: Get help with your online Home Office application
What type of help you can get
chunks.html_content: You cannot get immigration advice, or information about the status of an application, through this service. Contact UK Visas and Immigration to check the progress of an application you’ve already submitted.
